===Etymology===
From {{etyl|gd|en}} {{m|gd|sluagh-ghairm||battle cry}}, from {{etyl|sga|en}} {{m|gd|slúag}}, {{m|gd|slóg||army}}, from {{etyl|cel-pro|en}} {{m|cel-pro|*slowgos||troop, army}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*slowgʰo-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*slowgo-||entourage}} + {{etyl|sga|en}} {{m|gd|gairm||a call, cry}}, from {{etyl|cel-pro|en}} {{m|cel-pro|*garman-}}, {{m|cel-pro|*garrman-||a call, shout}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ǵh₂r-smn-}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ǵh₂r-||to shout, call}}. Possible cognate with {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|garrio||chatter}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|cearu||sorrow, care}}.

