===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} A [[battle]] [[cry]] (original meaning).
#* '''1805''', Walter Scott, "The Lay of the Last Minstrel", IV. xxvii:
#*: To heaven the Border slogan rung,/ The English war-cry answer'd wide.
# A [[distinctive]] [[phrase]] of a [[person]] or [[group]] of [[people]].
#* {{RQ:Wodehouse Offing|XVIII|[Bertie Wooster:] “Right-ho,” I said, not much liking the assignment, but liking less the idea of endeavouring to thwart this incandescent aunt in her current frame of mind. Safety first, is the Wooster '''slogan'''.}}
# {{context|[[advertising]]|lang=en}} A [[catch phrase]] associated with the [[product]] or [[service]] being advertised.

